Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,Brotherhood
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 20
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,===============================================================

Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.57,0:01:33.30,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Edward, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.85,0:01:35.28,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,You've grown.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.24,0:01:38.89,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,I heard from Pinako...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.39,0:01:42.28,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,...that you attempted human transmutation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.78,0:01:46.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,After all this time, why did you come back now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.28,0:01:49.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,There's no place for you here anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.89,0:01:52.38,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.88,0:01:56.67,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you burn down my house?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.07,0:02:01.07,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We decided we wouldn't turn back anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.64,0:02:03.48,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We did it to show our determination-
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.48,0:02:04.68,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.38,0:02:06.68,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,You just didn't want to see it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.58,0:02:11.43,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted to escape your horrifying memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.85,0:02:15.65,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted to conceal all traces of the sin you committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.15,0:02:18.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.61,0:02:22.26,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,You're no different from a child who hides\Nhis sheets after wetting himself in his sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.45,0:02:25.49,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,You ran, didn't you, Edward?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.95,0:02:31.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What do {\i1}you{\i0} know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.23,0:02:34.62,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! You're sickening!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.94,0:02:40.38,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,He's so similar to the way I was when I was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.64,0:03:28.49,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't changed at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.49,0:03:31.26,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Not even a bit from the old days.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.25,0:03:36.86,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you come back sooner?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.37,0:03:39.82,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Trisha was always waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.90,0:03:49.97,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Pinako.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.97,0:03:50.89,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.62,0:03:54.07,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,The thing my sons transmuted...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.06,0:03:57.25,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Was it really Trisha?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.43,0:03:58.37,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.22,0:04:03.50,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,I told you. It didn't even look remotely human.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.50,0:04:05.07,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,I can't even call that thing Trisha-
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.07,0:04:07.18,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.12,0:04:11.35,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,For example, the color of her eyes and hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.56,0:04:15.81,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.15,0:04:18.47,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,You're telling me that wasn't her?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.09,0:04:26.65,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,You're telling me those boys lost their bodies by creating something that wasn't even their mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.69,0:04:32.70,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,What?! You can continue to function without food or sleep?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.70,0:04:36.21,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Yup, as long as this seal remains unscathed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.36,0:04:39.71,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing! You're literally immortal!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.62,0:04:41.59,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.57,0:04:45.13,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,My body is almost like a bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.68,0:04:48.09,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I heard it from Barry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.56,0:04:52.57,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to place a soul that doesn't belong on a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.14,0:04:56.04,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,If you force a soul on to one, it will eventually be rejected.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.60,0:05:01.03,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Whether that will be tomorrow or ten years later...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.03,0:05:02.85,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,...even I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.60,0:05:07.53,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,No way... then you have to find a way to get your body back as soon as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.53,0:05:14.31,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, if your body starts to deteriorate, can't you transfer your soul on to something else and continue to live?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.21,0:05:17.75,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,If you do that, you can stay the way you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.73,0:05:22.26,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,Without feeling pain or needing to eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.26,0:05:24.05,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,What a convenient body!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.22,0:05:25.88,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it's not convenient!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.88,0:05:27.60,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You don't even know anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.24,0:05:32.11,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.12,0:05:34.31,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Winry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.31,0:05:45.31,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Winry?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.82,0:05:46.76,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.74,0:06:00.50,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Geez... You and Brother always get mad before I ever can, so I never get to.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.67,0:06:03.76,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,It's because....
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.94,0:06:13.35,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,It seems this body can't sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.54,0:06:15.43,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.37,0:06:25.44,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be able to return to your old body, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.82,0:06:27.61,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.24,0:06:37.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Give me back my brother's body!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.03,0:06:40.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He's... He's the only family I've got!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.66,0:06:41.75,Default,White,0000,0000,0000,,Give it back?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.66,0:06:44.45,Default,White,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.45,0:06:47.59,Default,White,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who put your brother in that state.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.81,0:06:49.42,Default,White,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.52,0:06:51.52,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.18,0:06:54.78,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,You and I are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.78,0:06:56.78,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,Edward Elric!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.90,0:06:59.13,Default,Tucker,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.26,0:07:07.07,Default,Trisha,0000,0000,0000,,Edward... don't leave me like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.88,0:07:12.26,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Ed! You still asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.72,0:07:14.65,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Your dad's about to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.65,0:07:22.83,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Can I take this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.56,0:07:26.21,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,It's the only one that has all four of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.66,0:07:28.38,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Help yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.38,0:07:29.72,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.47,0:07:35.12,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,As a token of my gratitude, I'll tell you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.96,0:07:41.79,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Something terrible will happen in this country soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.57,0:07:44.48,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Flee to another country.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.98,0:07:48.41,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,That's not uncommon here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.83,0:07:53.79,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, there are kids who call this place home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.57,0:07:57.37,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say I didn't warn you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.38,0:08:01.66,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Hohenheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.48,0:08:04.92,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Come back every now and then for a meal, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.28,0:08:12.35,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,It's a shame, Pinako,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.35,0:08:15.58,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,that I won't be able to eat your cooking anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.09,0:08:42.54,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really going to dig that thing up?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.75,0:08:49.75,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Want to call it off?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.45,0:08:54.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's just that my joints are starting to hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.14,0:08:57.95,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because it's about to rain. Let's get this over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.15,0:09:17.91,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Ed!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.63,0:09:20.34,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,I told you so!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.88,0:09:29.11,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Let's stop this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.24,0:09:31.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.44,0:09:36.39,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't confirm it, I'll never be able to move forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.82,0:09:37.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.96,0:09:38.97,Default,Hohen,0000,0000,0000,,You ran, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.11,0:09:41.97,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,No way in hell am I going to run!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.19,0:10:40.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.88,0:10:43.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Mom had auburn hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.96,0:10:47.01,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This is black.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.86,0:10:52.87,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,The femur is way too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.01,0:10:57.19,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,The pelvis... This is a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.92,0:10:58.91,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.36,0:11:01.38,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Ed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.92,0:11:05.39,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,This is not your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.45,0:11:27.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. You cannot revive the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.19,0:11:29.94,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's a truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.20,0:11:34.38,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It was impossible from the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.18,0:11:39.31,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Ed, pull yourself together!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.31,0:11:41.16,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Snap out of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.02,0:11:46.19,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine, Granny...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.28,0:11:50.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Since that day, this has been the symbol of despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.02,0:11:53.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But now, it will lead me to a path with hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.02,0:11:58.94,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al can get his body back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.19,0:12:25.48,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, you've reached the Curtis'.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.20,0:12:27.66,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's you, Ed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.66,0:12:28.60,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.22,0:12:32.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... There was something I wanted to ask you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.48,0:12:34.26,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.89,0:12:36.89,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.89,0:12:38.13,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Speak clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.09,0:12:44.28,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's about the time you tried to revive your baby...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.98,0:12:49.41,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.96,0:12:55.67,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Master, the person Al and I transmuted was not our mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.94,0:13:00.38,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean? What are you trying to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.51,0:13:04.63,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The child that was created by your transmutation...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.16,0:13:07.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure it was your child?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.34,0:13:22.32,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.59,0:13:26.67,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,So my son and his wife helped a lot on the battlefield, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.45,0:13:29.45,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Good to know...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.69,0:13:39.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.43,0:13:42.59,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Where did Hohenheim say he was headed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.83,0:13:45.47,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows? He didn't mention a word about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.47,0:13:48.10,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I completely forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.10,0:13:51.16,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,I had an important message for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.16,0:13:52.40,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Message?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.40,0:13:53.35,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.94,0:13:56.53,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Trisha's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.28,0:14:02.87,Default,Trisha,0000,0000,0000,,Could you pass this on to him when he comes back?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.80,0:14:07.07,Default,Trisha,0000,0000,0000,,Please tell him I couldn't keep my promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.56,0:14:10.71,Default,Trisha,0000,0000,0000,,That I have to leave him first, and that I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.18,0:14:14.60,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A promise? What promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.60,0:14:15.76,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,No idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.45,0:14:19.48,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to make you do this, but could you tell him for me if you see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.48,0:14:20.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why do {\i1}I{\i0} have to do it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.31,0:14:25.46,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,He may not look it, but he's actually quite worried about you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.86,0:14:30.01,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'll deliver the message after I give him a good punch in the face.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.97,0:14:35.22,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going back to Central?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.22,0:14:37.99,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, just to get yelled at by Al,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.45,0:14:40.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,since I went and did a bunch of stuff without telling him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.57,0:14:47.53,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.73,0:14:49.23,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.74,0:14:50.71,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.71,0:14:52.51,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You're in ruins!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.31,0:14:55.83,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.83,0:14:58.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you guys doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.13,0:14:59.33,Default,Ling,0000,0000,0000,,Eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.58,0:15:04.17,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, just what happened to you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.73,0:15:10.31,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Homunculi and Barry the Chopper?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.31,0:15:14.21,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And on top of it all, a rejection reaction due to different souls and bodies, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.21,0:15:19.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Stretching the armor that's left...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.59,0:15:35.56,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al will be able to return to his old body, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.56,0:15:37.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.05,0:15:39.15,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If I say I'll get his body back, I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.13,0:15:44.21,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.28,0:15:49.38,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I dug up the thing we transmuted back in Resembool.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.34,0:15:54.80,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,W-Why did you do something like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.98,0:15:59.81,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, I discovered that what we transmuted wasn't Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.12,0:16:06.42,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,What? What does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.85,0:16:07.69,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,But we...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.05,0:16:11.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We transmuted something completely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.92,0:16:14.61,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,No way! Then I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.87,0:16:18.87,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And now, I'm also confident we can get your body back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.62,0:16:20.62,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.87,0:16:21.90,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.32,0:16:24.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But before I get into that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.87,0:16:33.30,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You remember the time we fought over who'd be m-marrying W-Winry... right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.52,0:16:36.93,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,The thing we talked about up on the roof?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.93,0:16:39.81,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. So you turned Al down?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.81,0:16:41.81,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.32,0:16:45.15,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And so, I have a question for you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.15,0:16:46.31,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you turn him down?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.99,0:16:51.65,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,"I don't want to marry a guy who's shorter than me."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.82,0:16:57.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't decide a man's worth by his height!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.88,0:16:58.68,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.68,0:17:02.20,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Does this have anything to do with getting Al's body back?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.22,0:17:10.26,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,To sum it up, if Al knows something I don't, and Winry remembers the same thing, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.26,0:17:12.52,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...it really happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.99,0:17:19.10,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Since he remembers something that really happened,\Nit means the soul affixed to that armor is the real Al's.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.45,0:17:26.11,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I could only get your soul,\NI was able to pull you back from that gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.60,0:17:33.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If I could pull your soul from the gate, then I should be able to get your body back the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.59,0:17:37.64,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Separated from each other, the body and soul still exist....
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.07,0:17:40.37,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Barry the Chopper!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.54,0:17:45.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al, try to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.72,0:17:49.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The time you were dragged into the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.83,0:17:53.92,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,That time...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.67,0:17:59.59,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,That was me! I was there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.63,0:18:03.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. So all I have to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.02,0:18:06.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...is pull your body out like I did with your soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.71,0:18:07.48,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.54,0:18:14.94,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I was watching you from that thing's point of view!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.27,0:18:19.32,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So it was you inside that thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.32,0:18:24.13,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,The soul probably didn't affix due to the rejection reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.76,0:18:30.35,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,So we didn't damage anyone's soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.00,0:18:35.26,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Elric.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.26,0:18:37.73,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Izumi Curtis is on the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.53,0:18:43.00,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I looked into the family lineages of both my husband and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.96,0:18:48.65,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, the skin and hair color of that child...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.18,0:18:52.52,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,...cannot possibly have come from the two of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.37,0:18:55.94,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,You were able to find something out, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.19,0:18:57.14,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.14,0:18:59.65,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Confidence that I'll be able to get Al's body back...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.26,0:19:03.38,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to revive the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.23,0:19:07.17,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.15,0:19:10.42,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't that I was missing something...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.17,0:19:13.71,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,...but rather it was impossible from the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.56,0:19:16.57,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Ed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.57,0:19:17.82,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.33,0:19:20.26,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.85,0:19:26.47,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,What did the master say?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.23,0:19:32.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really get it, but she thanked me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.64,0:19:42.40,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.34,0:19:48.79,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, I've been blaming myself nonstop since that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.98,0:19:51.33,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,That it was me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.24,0:19:55.14,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,...who put Mom in that state and killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.29,0:19:59.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Same goes for me, Al.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.88,0:20:01.73,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.40,0:20:04.99,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't kill Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.31,0:20:10.38,Default,Sig,0000,0000,0000,,Izumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.62,0:20:13.55,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I feel saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.55,0:20:17.94,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't kill our child twice...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.17,0:20:25.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But it's true that I put you in that state.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.25,0:20:29.10,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to get your body back, no matter what-
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.10,0:20:29.98,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.14,0:20:33.83,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We carry the same sin, since I approved of the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.37,0:20:36.99,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't talk as though it's all your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.91,0:20:39.84,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Trying to do everything by yourself...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.77,0:20:45.72,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired of other people having to suffer because of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.35,0:20:48.18,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Same with Mr. Hughes, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.06,0:20:53.60,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,When I heard about his death...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.16,0:20:59.94,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I felt from the bottom of my heart I didn't want to return to my body if other people would have to suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.04,0:21:04.78,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.02,0:21:08.62,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,...even if they don't have the body of humans...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.62,0:21:11.37,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,...I've been watching people who live according to the way they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.82,0:21:17.70,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I'm in this state, people around me interact with me as though I'm human.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.71,0:21:25.47,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I know my body's like a bomb, but even a body made of flesh could die from accident or disease at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.64,0:21:31.09,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,So in order to live a normal life,\Nthis body isn't all that inconvenient either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.52,0:21:33.47,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I've truly started to feel that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.36,0:21:35.05,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.52,0:21:37.98,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,...I can't stand it any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.09,0:21:45.29,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm... I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.53,0:21:48.48,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,...tired of spending nights by myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.55,0:21:55.27,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,That's my reason for wanting to return to my old body.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.33,0:21:58.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'll make it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.09,0:22:04.84,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,After I beat the shit out of that "truth" guy, I'm going to drag your body out of there!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.02,0:22:05.88,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.10,0:22:16.97,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.04,0:22:23.64,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Has he always had such a large back?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.71,0:24:03.29,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The figure of a wounded comrade hurries the man's steps,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.22,0:24:10.11,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,and the boy risks everything he has to escape a dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.28,0:24:15.74,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.74,0:24:19.39,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 21, The Fool's Progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.86,0:24:24.65,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,You shall be the one to open fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.65,0:24:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
